. I have two modules (serves as widgets) both using iconics, and my main project depends on these two modules. When gradle tries to resolve the dependencies to see if there is any conflicts, it fails because the version of the dependency is unspecified.  
Answering your question, yea, for this case I can merge the two modules together to be one but that would be a hack to me and it means all artifacts using icon fonts will have to be one artifact, which is not an option for me. 
I checked, it is not only the google material fonts but also other fonts would have the same issue. 
. One way for fixing this is to manually solve the version in my gradle build script as the following: 
eachDependency { details ->
        //multiple actions can be specified
        if (details.requested.group == 'Android-Iconics' && details.requested.name == 'iconics-core') {
            //changing the name:
            details.useTarget group: 'com.mikepenz', name: 'iconics-core', version: '1.7.8'
        }
    }
