@MFlisar  this can't be done. Menu does not extend from TextViewor ImageView. See this for reference:
https://github.com/mikepenz/Android-Iconics/issues/119
. @MFlisar yes, but you have to do it programmatically. What you have to do is, in the activity or fragment retrieve the navigation View that you are implementing and then get the menu and then the menuItem and finally you can set up your icon as a drawable https://github.com/mikepenz/Android-Iconics#use-as-drawable
Something like this:
java
Menu menuNav = navigationView.getMenu();
MenuItem menuItem = menuNav.findItem(R.id.your_nav_icon);
menuItem.setIcon(new IconicsDrawable(this).icon(Ionicons.the_icon_you_want));
Hope it helps.
