Icons are not static by nature, they are static only for the embedded font at one single time.
Let met explains with how I use the library and why error handling is needed.
In my application users can create custom commands to replace buttons in a remote screen. They can associate icons with the command and everything is saved on the cloud.
So when they use my application version 1 that propose community-material-typeface:1.7.22.1 they have let's say 534 icons available.
So for the moment no problem there's 534 icons, they can choose inside those, and the name of the icon is saved on the cloud.
Now in 3 months I update the application and community-material-typeface is now updated and contains 550 icons.
New users have the new version of the application they can now assign 550 icons. But when another user restore the cloud database and still have version 1 of the application he only have access to 534 icons.
Meaning for 16 icons that some other users may have used, he well see a null drawable undetectable by the application due to how failure are now handled.
And this is valid for anything that store the icon name outside of the application. You can not control what icons are available at the time they are displayed.. Then please tell me, how do you allow a user to assign an icon to something, store it in the cloud and allow restoration?
And even if not using name, but codepoint or anything else, that does not change the issue, at one point the user can have data that point to an icon that his version of the application does not have.
